reviews.text: Shared seating with strangers which wasn't very comfortable. After looking at the reviews we thought it was fully vegan/vegetarian but wasn't. Also forgot to give us the rice we ordered. Not given any napkins, wouldn't go back again, uncomfortable experience.
Food tasted good and not oily even the deep fried dishes.

Just reached Kowloon, waiting for hotel check in and spotted the sign from across the road, perfect!  A good stop off for anyone vegetarian or vegan, the monkey head mushrooms with mango and orange were so tasty!
Good food . Lots of vegetarian option. Great variety in mushrooms

I only bought sushi take away.  A box of sushi with 3 flavours at $30.  They were not in normal size and circle shape, I think they should be Onigiri but not sushi as the size was big in triangle shape.  One flavour was kim chi which was a little spicy and crispy.  Another two flavous were mashed pumpkin and taro which were soft and sweet.  The dried seaweed became soft after refrigerated.  Rice was soft too.

result.name: 從心素食

reviews.text:
裝修後整體水平提高好多 價位稍高 生意都變好 今次午飯時間全場滿座 上餐時間有啲長 但都好高質 今次唔記得上我個例湯但實在太飽就算啦 下次都會再來
其實都幾中意食佢哋地下啲便當/點心 但以前有得擺入我個ECOwrap 衣家除左啲飽 其他大部分都有即棄膠盒裝曬 勁唔環保 想食都冇計啦
下午茶正價食物有半價。。。食物質素唔錯👍👍

地理位置及交通方便，坐位舒適，員工有禮。

2019036
點了幾樣食品，意見如下

牛油果板卷
不錯，幾好吃，不過有啲鬆散，下次可以試吓其他卷物

煎鍋貼
簡單直接，好食，今次最滿意嘅菜式，要安歌

野菜玉子燒
台灣味嘅日式食品，因為上面有少少素鬆，都是要安歌

雞油菇猴頭菇
如果有白飯送就更加好啦

天婦羅拼盤
都係唔好喺唔係食天婦羅嘅地方食天婦羅呀，不過天婦羅跟個芥棘汁都幾好味

下次仲可以試埋其他前菜，今次天婦羅有似多咗，換個前菜可能更好

咁樣叫+1 370幾蚊，可刷卡。
尖東罕有的素食餐館，令我有發現新大陸之感！新派素食近年有取代傳統素食店趨勢！尤以利用日式素食寿司及刺身模式作為吸引年青一代，的確「從心」！此外亦維持了基本的中式齋菜項目，味道尚算不錯！每日的例湯味道濃郁可口，令我每到素食館必試的蛇羹，此處都有供應，我鄭重地向各位推介。
如有空每星期都會去品嚐

result.name: 九記打冷.小菜.粉麵 Nine Kee Chiu Chow Restaurant

reviews.text: Quick service, good food.
Good taste and reasonable price, clean and friendly service..I would certainly recommend!
Reasonably priced, decent food.

The place of interest to visit is Museum of History in Tsim Sha Tsui, in Chatham Road. We are not a typical tourist, nor a wealthy Hong Kong local. We have several days here, and I do not need to eat in poshy restaurants yet.

We check out a cafe-restaurant just diagonally across the Museum. The photos displayed on an external column show some previous clients having a great time. Behind the glass cabinet, are Lo Sui Ngo hung on hooks, and ofals in some trays. It promotes a few To Chan or set menu rice items which sounds interesting. The dining area is clean enough to entice us to walk in and finally ordered our brunch.

Well, the cooks and stuff are eating at one table, and they all look “clean” in appearance, so it gives us some added comfort. We order two set menu items - Cheng Hoi Lo Sui Ngo Fan (Cheng Hoi Goose marinated in special soy sauce with rice) and Shan Tau Sa Giong Gai Fan.(Shan TauChicken marinated in sand ginger spice with rice).

When the dishes are placed on the table, they look very different from the pictures in the promotional material. The side dishes of the set menus are “lumped” with the meat. One of the side dishes is supposedly Lo Sui Dan Dau Fu (Lo Sui Egg and Tofu); however, the Dau Fu pieces are used to raise up the meat pieces in order to jazz up the dishes so that they appear to be really good value for money. The seaweed soup is replaced by the soup of the day. Papaya soup.

Being the first customers of the day, the waitress that serves us says that she offers us a bonus - the goose drumstick, and chicken rice instead of plain rice.

The chicken is flavoursome, and the goose is passable. The Lo Sui Dan looks a bit anemic. I like my meat to have some fat, especially goose and duck. Fat gives the distinct flavour associated with the meat, and makes the meat smoother and less tough in texture.

I have difficulty in understanding why so many so called health conscious people eat food as things to keep them alive, instead of enjoy food as a life pleasure, which probably is “healthier” for mental wellbeing.

By the time we finish our meal, the restaurant/cafe is almost full. Before I leave, I check out the storage, preparation area, kitchen and the toilet. They do not get all the ticks in my assessment list. I am glad I have my food first before I did that.

For about AUD 20 for 2, it is reasonable and acceptable.

Wonton noodles, goose intestine noodles, Chiu Chow cold crab, pig blood cube all made to good delicious standard.  Seating is average comfortable.  Be prepared for PRC visitors speaking loud.  Drunkard??

reviews.text: 服務親切，牛雜麵口味不錯。不知是否港式的湯沒在過濾高湯的，湯喝到最後會有一些硬硬的底渣。
食物惹味，尤以鹵水鵝必食，正青根魚非常值得推薦，套餐抵食。地点方便

ボリュームのある麺でした‼️
36H$なので、安い💴✨👛です。
お茶🍵も無料で出ます。
メニューは中国語と英語です。
お客はほとんどが中国の人です‼️
好好吃😋食完一輪再叫多一輪！尖沙咀來說價錢非常便宜👍🏻👍🏻👍🏻下次一定會再幫襯過
老字號啲野冇セ進步，打冷勉強接受，鹵水鵝片鹹十老身。蠔餅可煎可油炸，都過得去，冇油益味。碟蝦漿通菜變左鹹菜。沙茶牛肉真正露出個師父唔係做潮菜，將菠蘿粒混入牛肉炒，真正茶餐廳手法，重收$108-, 難理解。
